node.text:
Today’s #FirstieFriday is this semester’s Brigade Commander, 1/C Jackie Booker Jr. from Orangeburg, S.C.! 

Midshipman Booker, the Varsity Baseball Team Manager and a member of the Stockdale Center Ethics Debate Team, chose #USNA because it was the only place he saw himself growing into his own potential so that he may then help others around them grow into theirs. Through positively impacting as many lives as possible, and motivating others to do the same, Midshipman Booker envisions the world changing for the better.

Looking back at his time at USNA, Midshipman Booker’s favorite memory is finishing Sea Trials with his company-mates, as it was the culminating event of his plebe year with his classmates. He said, “It was just amazing seeing how far we've all come since meeting each other on I-Day and looking back on all of the crazy, fun things that we were able to do and accomplish throughout the year.” He looks forward to looking back after graduation and seeing the positive impact he and his classmates have made after three years in Annapolis.

The quote that has inspired his leadership style the most is one by Simon Sinek that states, “There are leaders and there are those who lead. Leaders hold a position of power or influence. Those who lead inspire us.”

📸:1/C Duncan Stoner and 1/C Peter Pryharski
